al abilities</li><li>teaching respect for human rights and fundamental freedom</li><li>teach respect for the cultural values of the child and others</li><li>preparing the child for an active adult life.</li></ul><p>Children in home education must also take part in the exams of the Flemish Community's Examination Board at set times. Here they can obtain the necessary certificate to continue with home education.</p><ul><li>At the latest in the school year in which your child turns 13 before 1 January, your child must obtain the certificate of primary education.<br>Example 1: Your child turns 13 in 2022. Your child obtains the certificate no later than June 2023. Example 2: Your child turns 13 in 2023. Your child obtains the certificate in June 2024 at the latest.</li><li>At the latest in the school year in which your child turns 16 before 1 January, your child must obtain at least the certificate of first grade secondary education.<br>Example 1: Your child turns 16 in 2022. Your child obtains the first-grade secondary school certificate at the latest during the 2022-2023 school year.<br>Example 2: Your child turns 16 in 2023. Your child obtains the certificate of first grade secondary education at the latest during the 2023-2024 school year.</li></ul><p>The education inspectorate may inspect home education to check whether the minimum requirements have been met. If two consecutive inspections show that your home schooling does not comply, you are obliged to enrol your child in a school.</p>","nl":"<p>Inhoudelijk moet het huisonderwijs gericht zijn op:</p><ul><li>ontplooiing van de persoonlijkheid, talenten en geestelijke en lichamelijke vermogens van het kind</li><li>bijbrengen van eerbied voor de rechten van de mens en de fundamentele vrijheid</li><li>bijbrengen van eerbied voor de culturele waarden van het kind zelf en van anderen</li><li>voorbereiding van het kind op een actief leven als volwassene.</li></ul><p>Kinderen die huisonderwijs volgen moeten bovendien op 