 that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, the applicant has not been convicted of a criminal offence in a member state of the European Economic Area, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special recognition conditions</strong>:<ul><li>have sound procedures in place to organise the examination</li><li>have suitable technical personnel</li><li>organise a regulatory examination jury.</li></ul></li></ul><h2>Validity period and obligations<strong> </strong></h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. The training centre must meet the following obligations among others to retain recognition:</p><ul><li>provide quality training</li><li>guarantee objectivity and independence</li><li>organise training and examinations as prescribed</li><li>have the necessary infrastructure in place to organise the examination</li><li>award certificates and submit the examination file to the competent authorities</li><li>hold insurance for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li></ul>","en-x-generated":"<p>To be recognised as a training centre, it must comply with:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all environmental recognitions<ul><li>in the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not received a criminal conviction in a <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">member state of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special conditions of recognition: </strong><ul><li>have sound procedures to organise examinations</li><li>have suitable technical staff</li><li>set up a regulatory examination jury.</li></ul></li></ul><p>More info on the conditions of recognition can be found in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058&amp;woLang=nl\">Article 8 VLAREL (general conditions of recognition)</a> and:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36102&amp;woLang=nl\">Article 21 VLAREL (special recognition conditions training centre technicians liquid fuel)</a>;</li><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36103&amp;woLang=nl\">Article 22 VLAREL (special conditions of approval for training centre technicians for gaseous fuel)</a>;</li><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36104&amp;woLang=nl\">Article 23 VLAREL (special conditions of approval for heating technician training centre)</a>. </li></ul><h2>Period of validity and obligations</h2><p>Recognition is valid for<strong> an indefinite</strong> period. However, a recognised training centre must meet a number of <strong>user requirements </strong>(=obligations) in order to retain its recognition.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-opleidingscentra-technici-gasvormige-brandstof-vloeibare-brandstof-of-verwarmingsaudit\">More info on the usage requirements for accredited training centres for gaseous fuel technicians, liquid fuel technicians and heating audit technicians</a>. </p>","nl-BE-x-formal":"<p>Om erkend te worden als opleidingscentrum, moet het voldoen aan:</p><ul><li><a 